- OpenAI API account with credits loaded - Google Drive account with API access enabled - Cloud storage account (Backblaze B2 or Wasabi - fastest to set up) - N8N Cloud trial account (easier than self-hosting for day 1) - 10-20 sample courses for testing ## 3. Hour-by-Hour Implementation Plan ### Hour 1: Account Setup (9:00 AM - 10:00 AM) **Tasks:** - [ ] Create N8N Cloud trial account - [ ] Set up Backblaze B2 or Wasabi storage bucket - [ ] Get OpenAI API key - [ ] Enable Google Drive API - [ ] Test all API connections **Expected Output:** All accounts created and credentials ready ### Hour 2: First Workflow - File Upload (10:00 AM - 11:00 AM) **Build N8N Workflow #1: Upload to Cloud** ``` Workflow Nodes: 1. Webhook Trigger (manual start) 2. Read Files from Folder 3. Upload to Cloud Storage 4. Log Success/Failures ``` **Test:** Upload 5 sample files successfully ### Hour 3: Audio Transcription Pipeline (11:00 AM - 12:00 PM) **Build N8N Workflow #2: Transcribe Audio** ``` Workflow Nodes: 1. Watch Cloud Storage Folder 2. Filter Audio Files (.mp3, .mp4) 3. OpenAI Whisper API Call 4. Save Transcript to Text File 5. Upload to Google Drive ``` **Test:** Transcribe 2 audio files end-to-end ### Hour 4: PDF Processing (12:00 PM - 1:00 PM) **Build N8N Workflow #3: Extract PDF Text** ``` Workflow Nodes: 1. Watch for PDF Files 2. Extract Text (N8N PDF node) 3. Format and Clean Text 4. Save to Google Drive ``` **Test:** Process 3 PDF files ### Hour 5: Basic Document Consolidation (2:00 PM - 3:00 PM) **Build N8N Workflow #4: Combine Content** ``` Workflow Nodes: 1. Collect All Processed Files by Course Folder 2. Combine Transcripts + PDF Content 3. Basic Markdown Formatting 4. Create Single Master Document per Course 5. Upload to Google Drive ``` **Test:** Create 1 complete consolidated course document ### Hour 6: Error Handling & Retry Logic (3:00 PM - 4:00 PM) **Add to All Workflows:** - Retry failed API calls (3 attempts) - Error notifications (email or Slack) - Failed file tracking - Resume capability **Test:** Simulate failures and verify recovery ### Hour 7: Batch Processing Setup (4:00 PM - 5:00 PM) **Scale Up Workflows:** - Connect all workflows together - Add queue management - Set up parallel processing (3-5 files at once) - Create simple progress log **Test:** Process 10 courses completely ### Hour 8: Documentation & Next Steps (5:00 PM - 6:00 PM) **Final Tasks:** - Document what's working and what's not - Export all N8N workflows as backup - Create simple user guide for running the system - Identify bottlenecks and improvement areas - Plan for scaling to full 1000 courses ## 4. Essential N8N Workflows (Copy-Paste Ready) ### Workflow 1: File Monitor & Upload **Purpose:** Watch folder, upload files to cloud storage **Key Nodes:** - Schedule Trigger (every 10 minutes) - Execute Command (list files in folder) - HTTP Request (upload to cloud storage API) - Set (log processed files) ### Workflow 2: Audio Transcription **Purpose:** Transcribe audio/video files using Whisper **Key Nodes:** - Cloud Storage Trigger (new audio file) - HTTP Request (OpenAI Whisper API) - Code (format transcript) - Google Drive (save transcript) ### Workflow 3: PDF Text Extraction **Purpose:** Extract text from PDF documents **Key Nodes:** - Cloud Storage Trigger (new PDF) - Extract from PDF (N8N built-in node) - Code (clean formatting) - Google Drive (save extracted text) ### Workflow 4: Content Consolidation **Purpose:** Combine all course content into one document **Key Nodes:** - Google Drive Trigger (monitor processed files folder) - Read Multiple Files - Merge Content (Code node) - Format as Markdown - Google Drive (create final document) ## 5. Quick Reference: API Credentials Setup ### OpenAI Whisper API Setup ``` 1. Go to platform.openai.com 2. Create API key 3. Add $20 minimum credits 4. Copy key to N8N credentials 5. Test with sample audio file ``` ### Google Drive API Setup ``` 1. Go to console.cloud.google.com 2. Create new project 3. Enable Google Drive API 4. Create OAuth credentials 5. Authorize in N8N ``` ### Backblaze B2 Setup (Fastest) ``` 1. Sign up at backblaze.com/b2 2. Create bucket 3. Generate application key 4. Note: keyID, applicationKey, bucketName 5. Configure in N8N HTTP Request node ``` ## 6. Minimum Viable Workflow Architecture **Simple Processing Flow:** ``` External Drive Files ↓ [Manual Upload Batch via N8N] ↓ Cloud Storage (Backblaze B2) ↓ [Automatic Processing] ├── Audio/Video → Whisper API → Transcript.txt ├── PDF → Text Extraction → Content.txt └── Other Files → Copy as-is ↓ [Consolidation Script] ↓ Combined_Course_Document.md ↓ Google Drive (organized by course) ``` ## 7. File Type Processing Table | File Type | N8N Node | Processing Time | Output Format | |-----------|----------|-----------------|---------------| | .mp3 | OpenAI Whisper API | ~1 min per hour | .txt transcript | | .mp4 | OpenAI Whisper API | ~2 min per hour | .txt transcript | | .pdf | Extract PDF | <1 second | .txt content | | .docx | Microsoft Office | <1 second | .txt content | | .txt | Read File | <1 second | Pass through | ## 8. Testing Checklist **After Each Hour - Verify:** - [ ] Workflow runs without errors - [ ] Files successfully processed - [ ] Output looks correct - [ ] Credentials still working - [ ] No API rate limit issues - [ ] Progress is logged **End of Day Success Criteria:** - [ ] 10+ courses fully processed - [ ] All workflows saved and backed up - [ ] Can process more courses by clicking \"Execute Workflow\" - [ ] Transcripts are readable and accurate - [ ] Files organized in Google Drive - [ ] Know how to troubleshoot common errors ## 9. Common Issues & Quick Fixes ### Issue: API Timeout Errors **Fix:** Add retry logic with 30-second delays between attempts ### Issue: File Upload Fails **Fix:** Check file size limits, may need to split large files ### Issue: Whisper API Returns Empty **Fix:** Verify audio file format is supported (MP3, MP4, WAV only) ### Issue: N8N Workflow Won't Execute **Fix:** Check all credential connections, re-authenticate if needed ### Issue: Out of API Credits **Fix:** Add more OpenAI credits or switch to AssemblyAI temporarily ## 10. What to Do After Day 1 **If System is Working:** - Process next 50 courses overnight - Monitor for errors in the morning - Optimize slow workflows - Add quality checks **If System Needs Work:** - Focus on the failing workflow - Test with simpler files first - Review error logs carefully - Consider hiring expert for completion ## 11. Essential N8N Nodes for This Project **Must Know Nodes:** - **Schedule Trigger:** Run workflow automatically - **Webhook Trigger:** Start workflow manually - **HTTP Request:** Call APIs (Whisper, Cloud Storage) - **Code (JavaScript):** Custom data processing - **Read/Write Files:** File operations - **Google Drive:** Upload/organize files - **Split Out:** Process arrays of files - **Merge:** Combine data streams ## 12. Rapid Implementation Tips ### Speed Optimization: ✅ Use N8N Cloud (no server setup time) ✅ Start with Backblaze B2 (fastest account creation) ✅ Use OpenAI Whisper (best accuracy, least troubleshooting) ✅ Process smallest files first (faster feedback loop) ✅ Skip advanced formatting initially (focus on working system) ### What to Skip on Day 1: ❌ Perfect error handling (basic retry is enough) ❌ Advanced monitoring dashboards (logs are sufficient) ❌ Multi-format exports (Markdown only is fine) ❌ Cost optimization (focus on functionality first) ❌ Beautiful document formatting (get content first) ## 13. Sample Test Data Structure **Prepare 10-20 Test Courses Like This:** ``` Test_Course_01/ ├── intro.mp3 (5-10 min) ├── module1.mp4 (10-15 min) ├── slides.pdf (5-10 pages) └── notes.docx Test_Course_02/ ├── overview.mp3 ├── tutorial.mp4 └── workbook.pdf ``` **Why This Works:** - Small files = fast processing - Mix of formats = tests all workflows - Manageable size = see results quickly ## 14. Emergency Shortcuts **If Behind Schedule:** **Hour 1-2 Behind?** → Skip cloud storage, process files directly from external drive **Hour 3-4 Behind?** → Focus on transcription only, skip PDF processing **Hour 5-6 Behind?** → Manual document consolidation, automate later **Hour 7-8 Behind?** → Process 3-5 courses successfully, document the process, expand tomorrow ## 15. Success Metrics for Day 1 | Metric | Minimum Target | Good Target | Excellent Target | |--------|----------------|-------------|------------------| | Courses Processed | 5 | 10 | 20 | | Workflows Created | 2 | 4 | 5 | | Transcription Accuracy | 85% | 90% | 95% | | System Uptime | 70% | 85% | 95% | | Documentation Complete | Basic | Detailed | Comprehensive | ## 16. Post-Day 1 Action Plan **Tomorrow Morning:** - Review all processed courses - Fix any obvious errors - Start processing next batch (50-100 courses) - Monitor system for 2 hours - Optimize bottlenecks **This Week:** - Scale to 200-300 courses - Add advanced error handling - Implement quality checks - Create better document templates **This Month:** - Process all 1000 courses - Perfect the output format - Create comprehensive documentation - Train on system maintenance --- ## Quick Start Command List **N8N Workflow Export Command:** ``` Settings → Workflow → Download ``` **Test API Connection:** ``` N8N → Credentials → Test ``` **View Execution Logs:** ``` N8N → Executions → View Details ``` **Manual Workflow Trigger:** ``` Workflow → Execute Workflow ``` --- ## Contact & Support Resources **N8N Community:** - Forum: community.n8n.io - Discord: discord.gg/n8n - Documentation: docs.n8n.io **OpenAI Support:** - Status: status.openai.com - Documentation: platform.openai.com/docs **Emergency Troubleshooting:** - Check API status pages first - Review N8N execution logs - Test credentials individually - Restart workflows if stuck --- Make this document clean, fast to scan, with clear hour-by-hour breakdown. Use simple tables, checkbox lists, and code blocks. Focus on ACTION not theory. No budget discussions, no multi-language support, no legal sections. Just \"here's what to do, hour by hour, to get it working TODAY\". View Perfect! I've created a streamlined 1-day rapid implementation guide that's laser-focused on getting you working TODAY. Here's what makes this version different: Key Features of the 1-Day Version: ✅ Ultra-Focused Approach: 8-hour timeline broken down hour by hour No budget discussions - just technical implementation No legal/compliance sections - just building the system Single language only - English transcription focus Immediate action orientation - every section is \"do this now\" 📋 Hour-by-Hour Breakdown: Hour 1 (9-10 AM): Set up all accounts and test credentials Hour 2 (10-11 AM): Build first workflow - file upload to cloud Hour 3 (11 AM-12 PM): Audio transcription pipeline with Whisper Hour 4 (12-1 PM): PDF text extraction workflow Hour 5 (2-3 PM): Basic document consolidation Hour 6 (3-4 PM): Error handling and retry logic Hour 7 (4-5 PM): Batch processing setup and scaling Hour 8 (5-6 PM): Documentation and next steps planning 🎯 What's Included: Pre-flight checklist - what you need before starting Step-by-step N8N workflows - exactly which nodes to use Quick API setup guides - copy-paste credential setup File type processing table - know what to expect Testing checklist - verify after each hour Common issues & fixes - troubleshooting guide Emergency shortcuts - if you fall behind schedule Success metrics - know if you're on track ⚡ Speed Optimizations: What to DO on Day 1: ✅ Use N8N Cloud (skip server setup) ✅ Process smallest files first ✅ Focus on working system over perfect formatting ✅ Test with 10-20 courses only What to SKIP on Day 1: ❌ Advanced monitoring dashboards ❌ Perfect error handling ❌ Multiple export formats ❌ Beautiful document formatting ❌ Cost optimization 📊 Realistic Success Targets: Metric\tMinimum\tGood\tExcellent Courses Processed\t5\t10\t20 Workflows Created\t2\t4\t5 System Uptime\t70%\t85%\t95% 🚀 Post-Day 1 Plan: Tomorrow: P